{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e5e23632-31d7-41f0-8616-0e0c824ec4e3","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **4.6.0+** (you're already there ✓)\n\n2. **Replace `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** with:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.NUnit\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add to your `.csproj`**:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Enable the entry point** — add a `Program.cs` or use the source-generated one by adding:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly as an executable (`dotnet run` / the built binary).\n\n**Key differences to note:**\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` runs tests as a standalone app (not hosted by `vstest.console`).\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply; check for equivalents in the new platform's configuration.\n- Extensions like code coverage or TRX reporting need their own `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.*` packages.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f890077c-9563-4dce-bcd1-1c6a062fc4fa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure migration. I don't need to search the codebase for this - I can provide the answer directly based on my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about what they need to change.","outputTokens":437,"requestId":"285D:3577AF:155CF9A:16C4022:6A045FC9"},"id":"2e0f48e1-86ff-4430-8159-cf795930f52c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:16.036Z","parentId":"0ef3422e-1633-45fb-9949-14055424c31d"}
